If you have any questions about the status of your FOIPA request, please e-mail foipaquestions@ic.fbi.gov<mailto:foipaquestions@ic.fbi.gov>.



FIND STATUS OF FOIPA- LAST UPDATED ON January 18, 2017



Please enter the whole FOIPA number-Example: [1234567-000]



FOIPA:

Results will show the Request Number, Case Type and Process Description shown below:

FOIPA:

1234567-000

Case Type:

FOIPA

Process Description (Will display the current progress of the request)

The FBI’s FOIPA Program is searching the FBI’s indices for potentially responsive documents.

You may be contacted via formal letter for all fees and/or negotiation issues that may apply.
NOTE: Recent requests are entered into the FOIPA database in the order that they are received. Before you can check the status, you must have received correspondence assigning a FOIPA request number and the information transferred to the online database. Status information is updated weekly. If a request has been closed within the last six months the online database will display the following: The FOIPA number entered has been closed, and appropriate correspondence has been sent to the address on file.

Estimated Dates of Completion

Requests are processed in the order in which they are received through our multi-track processing system, and the FBI receives a voluminous amount of requests on a daily, weekly, monthly, and annual basis.  Requests are divided into two primary tracks--simple (under 50 pages of potentially responsive documents) and complex (over 50 pages of potentially responsive documents).  Our complex requests are further divided into medium, large, and extra-large sub-tracks.  Simple track requests typically require the least amount of time to process.



Currently, simple track cases average approximately 181 days from the date of receipt for processing.  Requests in the medium processing track are currently averaging 232 days from the date of receipt for processing, those in the large processing track are currently averaging approximately 659 days, and those in the extra-large track are averaging 998 days.


Thank you,

communications.subject: RE: Freedom of Information Request #1334485-001
communications.communication: It has been over a year since payment was made. I would appreciate release of responsive materials in part, if possible. An update on anticipated release of all responsive materials would be appreciated. Thank you!

communications.subject: RE: Freedom of Information Request #1334485-001
communications.communication:
Good afternoon,

Our records reflect no posted payment associated with 1334485-001; rather, your request was reopened on 11-20-2015 upon receipt of your cost letter response reflecting commitment to pay the estimated fees.  No fees have been formally assessed related to this request to date.

As indicated on our Status Update website, http://vault.fbi.gov under the “Check Status of Your FOI/PA Request” link, your request is presently awaiting assignment to a Disclosure analyst who will then review the records to determine if any redactions are required pursuant to subsections of Title 5, U. S. Code, Section 552 and 552a.  Please continue to check the status of your request using the provided website, as statuses are updated weekly.

Requests are processed in the order in which they are received through our multi-track processing system, and the FBI receives a voluminous amount of requests on a daily, weekly, monthly, and annual basis.  Requests are divided into two primary tracks--simple (under 50 pages of potentially responsive documents) and complex (over 50 pages of potentially responsive documents).  Complex requests are further divided into medium, large, and extra-large sub-tracks based upon request size.  Simple track requests typically require the least amount of time to process.

Your request is currently in the complex request large processing track, and the estimated date of completion for your request is March 2018.

Our records reflect in April 2016, the negotiation analyst made two attempts to contact you regarding the option to potentially reduce the scope of your request in an effort to receive the records more quickly; no response was received at the time.  Please be advised reducing the scope of your request can accelerate the process as it could potentially place your request in a quicker processing track.  This may also reduce any search and duplication costs, if applicable, and allow for a more timely receipt of your information.  If you wish to discuss reducing the scope of your request, please notify us in writing.

Please contact foipaquestions@fbi.gov<mailto:foipaquestions@fbi.gov> if you require further assistance.

Thank you,


Holly Early
Government Information Specialist
Record/Information Dissemination Section (RIDS)
FBI-Records Management Division

communications.subject: FOIA request 1334485-001 / Passive Optical Network
communications.communication:
Good afternoon Mr. Peck,

We're contacting you in reference to the FOIPA request number included in the subject line of this email.  The FBI located approximately 3344 pages potentially responsive to your request. 

Requests are processed in the order in which they are received through our multi-track processing system:
Small track requests (0-50 pages) current average time is approximately 4 months to complete;
Medium track requests (51-500 pages) current average time is approximately 41 months to complete;
Large track requests (501-4,999 pages) current average time is approximately 67 months to complete; and
Extra-large track requests (over 5,000 pages) current average time is approximately 79 months to complete.

The current average time to complete your large track request is at least XX months. Reducing the scope of your request may accelerate the processing, allow for a timelier receipt of the information you seek, and reduce the duplication costs, if applicable.  Would you be willing to consider reducing the scope of your request to place it in a smaller, potentially faster processing track?
Please let us know if this is something you would be interested in further discussing. If you chose to narrow the scope of your request, you will be able to request remaining material via a new FOIPA request submission at the completion of this request, subject to applicable fees.

Best regards,

Negotiation Team
Federal Bureau of Investigation
Fbi.foipa.negotiation@fbi.gov<mailto:Fbi.foipa.negotiation@fbi.gov>

Status Checks: https://vault.fbi.gov/fdps-1/@@search-fdps | foipaquestions@fbi.gov<mailto:foipaquestions@fbi.gov>
For additional information, please visit the www.fbi.gov/foia<http://www.fbi.gov/foia> website.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Bethel School District – Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including District Responses for the years 2010 - 2021
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act [RCW 42.56] I hereby request the following records:

I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by Bethel School District and a complete electronic copy of the District's Responses to these Public Records Requests for the time period January 1, 2010 through November 4, 2021.

In the event the District chooses to provide these records in installments over time I request the records to be produced in reverse chronological order - from the most recent records to the earliest.

If this request is denied in whole or part, I ask that you justify all deletions by reference to specific exemptions of the PRA. I also request a detailed contemporaneous log to be provided for any document withheld or redacted.

For each responsive record the District contends is exempt from public disclosure, in whole or in part, please specifically identify the record by subject, title, author, custodian and date, and state how a specific statutory exemption applies to each record as required by RCW 42.56.210(3) and Rental Housing Ass'n v. Des Moines, 165 Wn.2d 525, 199 P.3d 393 (2009).

I request electronic production of all electronic records in the original NATIVE electronic format for each record. 

I request for these public records to be produced by public (no password) e-mail attachment or link. If electronic attachment or link is not possible, an alternative would be to produce responsive records via USB DRIVE or DATA CD-ROM.

THIS REQUEST IS NOT BEING MADE FOR COMMERCIAL PURPOSES.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

PRA Audit

parents with regard to their children/students.

I may be reached at 253-800-2043.

Sincerely,

Kathryn Kemp
Human Resources Manager
Public Records Officer
Workers' Compensation
Office 253-800-2043
Fax 253-800-2049

 You don't get injured workers well to put them back to work, you put them
back to work to get them well.  ~* Richard Pimental*

communications.subject: RE: Washington Public Records Act Request: Bethel School District – Request for a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by the District including District Responses for the years 2010 - 2021
communications.communication:
Hello Ms. Kemp,

Thank you for your email.

We would appreciate any questions you may have to be sent via email. 

In response to your query regarding parents/students:

Presumably, virtually an entire student’s educational file would be exempt from any public records request. 

We would agree to exclude records requests made by parents/guardians about their students for their student’s grades and educational file.

Thank you.

I don't understand your "communication informing you of our need for an
extension" including "clarification."

Here is the original request:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act [RCW 42.56] I hereby request the following records:

I request a complete electronic copy of all Public Records Requests received by Bethel School District and a complete electronic copy of the District's Responses to these Public Records Requests for the time period January 1, 2010 through November 4, 2021.

Des Moines, 165 Wn.2d 525, 199 P.3d 393 (2009).

I request electronic production of all electronic records in the original NATIVE electronic format for each record.

if not,

PROBLEM.

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, this is a request for records related to this agency’s receipt of and response to public records requests. 

For the period from January 1, 2018 through December 31, 2023, please provide all logs and available related details of public records requests received by this office. Responsive materials include those that describe the following details for each public records request received by this office: 
The name of the requester and the affiliated organization
The date on which the request was received by this office
A description of the requested records
The tracking number assigned by this office to the request
The date on which the request was closed by this office
The final disposition of the request, including, if possible, whether the request was fully fulfilled, partially fulfilled, rejected in its entirety, resulted in no responsive documents, or remains open
Details on exemptions applied to responsive and withheld records
The number of released pages

Please provide the responsive materials in the form of a spreadsheet (either in CSV or XLS file formats), if possible. 

This request is being made as part of an academic and journalistic project and is not being made for any commercial reason. In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request be fulfilled electronically, via e-mail attachment, the upload link in the footer of this message, or Dropbox, if possible.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Please contact me if your office has any questions about this request. 

Sincerely,

Beryl Lipton

communications.subject: [Records Center] Public Records Request :: R000806-011624
communications.communication:
--- Please respond above this line --- 
RE: Public Records Request of January 16, 2024, Reference # R000806-011624 Dear Beryl Lipton, The Washington State Patrol has received yourpublic disclosure request regarding: “To Whom It May Concern: 

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, this is a request for records related to this agency’s receipt of and response to public records requests. 

For the period from January 1, 2018 through December 31, 2023, please provide all logs and available related details of public records requests received by this office. Responsive materials include those that describe the following details for each public records request received by this office: 
The name of the requester and the affiliated organization 
The date on which the request was received by this office 
A description of the requested records 
The tracking number assigned by this office to the request 
The date on which the request was closed by this office 
The final disposition of the request, including, if possible, whether the request was fully fulfilled, partially fulfilled, rejected in its entirety, resulted in no responsive documents, or remains open 
Details on exemptions applied to responsive and withheld records 
The number of released pages 

Please provide the responsive materials in the form of a spreadsheet (either in CSV or XLS file formats), if possible. 

This request is being made as part of an academic and journalistic project and is not being made for any commercial reason. In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request be fulfilled electronically, via e-mail attachment, the upload link in the footer of this message, or Dropbox, if possible. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires. 

Please contact me if your office has any questions about this request. 

Sincerely, 

Beryl Lipton 

Upload documents directly: https://accounts.muckrock.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.muckrock.com%2Faccounts%2Flogin%2F%3Fnext%3D%252Faccounts%252Fagency_login%252Fwashington-state-patrol-211%252Fstate-police-agency-foi-request-log-2018-2023-washington-state-patrol-157110%252F%253Femail%253Dpubrecs%252540wsp.wa.gov&url_auth_token=AAAawGGLxe-9Y0NPUyYIdtZutX0%3A1rPw6A%3ASWancdjVtEQ8INGyEsO9Y1iLvhlYhEQniIXqnN68ny8” Please note that public records requests are only held for 2 years so we only have information dating back until 01/01/22 unless the request is still being worked on. Pursuant to RCW 42.56.520, this is notification that we are searching our records to determine the location, nature, and amount of records, if any, that may be responsive to your request.  If responsive records are found we estimate that we can make available an installment of records on or before 03/04/24.  If records are ready prior to that time, you will be notified.  If the time assessment requires adjustment, you will also be notified. Should you have any questions, please let us know. Sincerely, Rhonda Tucker, Public Records Manager

communications.subject: New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. All email correspondence, with attachments, mentioning "Water Property Investors," "Water Property Investor II," or "Water Property Investor III." 

2. Pitch decks, prospectuses, or any other materials provided to NMERB by the the above funds for consideration of potential investments.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 15 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Julia Rock

communications.subject: Fw: [EXTERNAL] New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
Dear Records Requestor:


Your request for information from the New Mexico Educational Retirement Board was forwarded to me. In accordance with the New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act (IPRA), “a written request shall provide the name, address and telephone number of the person seeking access to the records and shall identify the records sought with reasonable particularity.” Section 14-2-8(C) NMSA 1978.


If you will provide me with your name and mailing address, we can begin the process of allowing inspection of the relevant records.


The Inspection of Public Records Act can be found at 14-2-1 through 14-2-12 NMSA 1978.


Thank you.


Amanda Olsen



Amanda Olsen, Paralegal
NM Educational Retirement Board

Dear Mr. Scroggins and Ms. Olsen,

Thanks for the update. Can you provide any additional info regarding the source of delays on this request, or the estimated delivery date? Please feel free to give me a call at 781-962-8816 if it'd be helpful to discuss the scope of the materials we're requesting.

communications.subject: RE: New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
Dear Ms. Rock,

I am responding to your email yesterday requesting any additional info regarding the source of delays on this request. Please be assured that we make every effort to respond promptly to every request. However, we must also ensure that we are diligent and accurate in our reply. Thus, when obtained, all documents and emails must be reviewed. Additionally, we must rely on the state agency that controls the entire state email system to identify and provide the emails requested. As you can imagine, the process takes time.

As to an estimated response date, in our letter of August 1, 2023, we noted that we intend to respond by September 6, 2023.

Thank you for your patience and please feel free to contact me if you have further questions.

Respectfully,

[cid:image001.png@01D9C623.0D3F7D80]

communications.subject: ATTORNEY CLIENT PRIVILEGED - RE: [EXTERNAL] RE: New Mexico Inspection of Public Records Act Request: Water Asset Management funds correspondence
communications.communication:
Dear Ms. Rock and Ms. Burns,

Thank you for your inquiry and please accept our apologies for the delay.

As Mr. Scroggins noted in his August 3, 2023 email regarding our projected response, we always try to be prompt.  But as you might guess, the request references a large number of records.  As he said, we must thoroughly review all records to identify and obtain the responsive documents from both external and internal sources.  It is a complex and time-consuming process.

I am confident that we will have documents ready to provide on or before the December 6th, 2023, date noted in our recent communication.

Thank you for your continued patience!
Regards,
Renee

title: Public Records Request: Sown to Grow

communications.subject: Tennessee Public Records Act Request: Public Records Request: Sown to Grow
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All contracts, licenses, MOUs, MOAs, data agreements, letters of intent, State of Work documents, Scope of Work documents, and other agreement documents with Sown to Grow between 1/1/2018 and 1/1/2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with e.

communications.subject: Thank you for your Open Records Request
communications.communication:
"Dear Requester, 

 

 

This message is intended to acknowledge Shelby County Schools’ receipt of your recently submitted public records request, which is reflected below. 

 

 

 

 

Your Open Records Request has been received; however, due to COVID-19, please expect response time to your request to be slower than normal.

 

 

 

SCS appreciates your patience as it navigates continuity of operations in light of COVID-19.

 

 

 

Due to the upcoming Christmas Break, Shelby County Schools will respond to all requests submitted between December 19 - 22, 2020, on January 4, 2021.   Open Records Requests will not be accepted December 23, 2020, - January 3, 2021.  The Open Records Request Portal will reopen on January 4, 2021.

 

 

 

 

 

 

We apologize for any inconvenience.

 

 

Thank you!

Public Records Request Coordinator

Shelby County Schools"

communications.subject: MSCS - OPEN RECORDS REQUEST - Receipt #0002127 - January 27, 2024 - REVIEW IN PROGRESS / DELAY IN RESPONSE
communications.communication:
Good afternoon, Mr. Hoover.  Please be advised that there will be a delay in the processing of your Open Records Request as referenced above.  It is not practicable for the records you have requested to be made promptly available for inspection and/or copying because:

1.      it has not yet been determined that records responsive to your request exist OR
2.      the office is still in the process of retrieving, reviewing, and/or redacting the requested records.

The time reasonably necessary to produce the record(s) or information and/or to make a determination of a proper response to your request is expected to be on or about Friday, April 12, 2024.  If records exist, we will let you know about the estimated costs (if any) associated with your request.

Please note, in an effort to limit in-person contact due to COVID-19, Shelby County Board of Education's response time to requests and processing will be slower than normal.  Memphis-Shelby County Schools appreciates your patience as it navigates continuity of operations in light of COVID-19.  Further, please be advised that expected dates of delivery are subject to change.

If you have any additional questions regarding your records request, please contact OpenRecordsRequests@scsk12.org<mailto:OpenRecordsRequests@scsk12.org> and reference the receipt number indicated in the subject line.

Sincerely,

communications.subject: Nevada Public Records Act Request: Washoe County Sheriff - Drone Program
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Nevada Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

-All UAS (unmanned aerial systems) flight logs from 2023
-All written requests for UAS deployment from 2023

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ariel Smith

You can monitor the progress of your request at the link below and you'll receive an email when your request has been completed. Again, thank you for using the Public Records Center. The WCSO typically processes requests in the order of receipt.  The time it takes to respond to a request will vary depending on the complexity of the request and any backlog of requests already pending.  A simple request can be processed faster than one that is complex.  Simple requests are typically more targeted and seek fewer pages of records.  Complex requests typically seek a high volume of material or require additional steps to process.  Some requests are submitted for legal review for confidentiality and privilege, which increases the time for processing. Your request will be forwarded to the relevant department(s) to locate the information you seek and to determine the volume and any costs associated with satisfying your request. Washoe County Sheriff's Office

communications.subject: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Charlene Humphreys/Hours Logged
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

All copy of all hours logged for Charlene Humphreys for CY2022.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Fecteau

communications.subject: RE: New York Freedom of Information Law Request: Charlene Humphreys/Hours Logged
communications.communication:
I am reaching out concerning my Freedom of Information Law (FOIL) requests, which I submitted over 20 business days ago. Regrettably, I have not received any response, leading me to interpret this lack of communication as a denial. In light of these circumstances, I am formally initiating an appeal.

Per the Freedom of Information Law, I am aware that the responsible entity for reviewing appeals must respond within 10 business days of receiving the appeal. Should my appeal be denied, I kindly request a comprehensive, written explanation elucidating the grounds for such denial, as mandated by legal requirements.

Lastly, I wish to underscore that the Freedom of Information Law mandates the forwarding of all appeals and subsequent determinations to the Committee on Open Government, Department of State, One Commerce Plaza, 99 Washington Ave., Albany, New York 12231.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Emails and other correspondence associated with Sen. Manka Dhingra's accounts.
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All email and electronic communications (including text messages from any issued phone) from Senator Manka Dhingra, pertaining to Rep. Nikki Torres, between the dates of July 1st, 2023 and January 10, 2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Andrew Corral

communications.subject: Public Records Request :: P001494-011024
communications.communication:
Dear Andrew Corral: 
Thank you for contacting the Washington State Legislature. Our office received your public records request on 1/10/2024 and we have assigned your request tracking number P001494-011024. Your request will be processed in accordance with Washington State's Public Records Act, Chapter 42.56 RCW. Records Requested: To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All email and electronic communications (including text messages from any issued phone) from Senator Manka Dhingra, pertaining to Rep. Nikki Torres, between the dates of July 1st, 2023 and January 10, 2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Andrew Corral

Upload documents directly: https://accounts.muckrock.com/accounts/login/?next=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.muckrock.com%2Faccounts%2Flogin%2F%3Fnext%3D%252Faccounts%252Fagency_login%252Fwashington-state-legislature-9751%252Funtitled-156863%252F%253Femail%253Dwaleg%252540govqa.us&url_auth_token=AAAS5elqAenAbbBtje-3bb0yNnA%3A1rNpAL%3AkV65dl0qzIQDbVVJ8JhzBJF8_AYVQAqwklwTSMdIXWU 
 
We will work with the appropriate Member office and/or department(s) to locate the records you seek and to determine the volume and any costs associated with satisfying your request. We will contact you about the availability and/or provide you with copies of the records in question. 
PLEASE NOTE: Washington State’s Public Records Act, Chapter 42.56 RCW, does not require a governmental body to create new information, do legal research, or answer general questions. For information about the Washington State Legislature and the legislative process, visit the Legislative Information Center or call (360) 786-7573.
 
You'll receive an email when your records are available. You can also monitor the progress of your request at the Wash. State Legislature’s Public Records Center. 
Again, thank you for using the Wash. State Legislature’s Public Records Center. 
Washington State Legislature

You requested the following: 
All email and electronic communications (including text messages from any issued phone) from Senator Manka Dhingra, pertaining to Rep. Nikki Torres, between the dates of July 1st, 2023 and January 10, 2024. 
Reasonable Estimate: 
Due to our current workload and other pending requests, we estimate having responsive records ready on or by February 12, 2024.  Records maybe provided in installments as appropriate. 

Reasonable Fees for Providing Copies of Public Records: 
The Senate may impose a reasonable fee for providing copies of public records as per RCW 42.56120(4) and our Senate Public Records Policy.  The Senate fee schedule can be found at the following link https://leg.wa.gov/Senate/Documents/SenateFeeSchedule.pdf. Sincerely, 
Senate Public Records

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Tampa Police Department, Tampa, FL Request
communications.communication:
To Whom it may concern,
Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:
Any and all records from the past year regarding your nuisance property ordinance that will be referred to as ordinance in this request but could be known (but not limited to) as Public Nuisance Abatement Board as described in Chapter 14, Article VIII, Sec. 14-291 of the city code.
Please provide any and all written records (including but not limited to hard-copy documents, memos, emails, word processor documents, PDF documents, PowerPoint files, images files, video files etc.) regarding the Ordinance including but not limited to:
• police calls, reports, citations, or arrests, collected by the municipality police department for the purpose of enforcing the ordinance
The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.
In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.
Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request.
Sincerely,
Jenny Wadhwa

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Expenses
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

I was seeking copies of any and all expense records for travel into the State of Nevada for the period 2020.  This would include but not be limited to reimbursements for mileage, gas, airfare, lodging, etc.  

Due to novel coronavirus emergency which requires so much teleworking in your agency as publicly stated repeatedly to this website, I think an overwhelming public interest exists in your spending and migration patterns. 

Your agency has expense disclosure transparency requirements based on The Federal Funding Accountability and Transparency Act FFATA, and The Digital Accountability and Transparency Act of 2014, DATA in addition to FOIA. 

As we have previously discussed sometimes these records are held within the Financial Management Division.  

But please search any and all available indices/records areas that would be likely to contain the records sought. 

Please produce the records in EFOIA Format .pdf document preferred.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

communications.subject: DEA FOIA/PA Case Number: 23-00303-F
communications.communication:
Dear William Fernandes: This e-mail responds to your Freedom of Information Act/Privacy Act (FOIA/PA) request dated April 2, 2022, received by the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA), FOIA/PA Unit, seeking access to DEA records.  Your request has been opened and assigned the following case number: 23-00303-F.  Please include this case number when communicating with this office. The records you seek require searches in another office or offices, and so your request falls within "unusual circumstances."  See 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(6)(B)(i)-(iii).  Because of these unusual circumstances, we are extending the time limit to respond to your request beyond the ten additional days provided by the statute.  We have not yet completed a search to determine whether there are records within the scope of your request.  The time needed to process your request will necessarily depend on the complexity of our records search and on the volume and complexity of any records located.  For your information, this office assigns incoming requests to one of three tracks:  simple, complex, or expedited.  Each request is then handled on a first-in, first-out basis in relation to other requests in the same track.  Simple requests usually receive a response in approximately one month, whereas complex requests necessarily take longer.  At this time, your request has been assigned to the complex track.  You may wish to narrow the scope of your request to limit the number of potentially responsive records or agree to an alternative time frame for processing, should records be located; or you may wish to await the completion of our records search to discuss either of these options. We regret the necessity of this delay, but please be assured that your request will be processed as soon as possible.  If you have any questions or wish to discuss reformulation or an alternative time frame for the processing of your request, you may contact FOIA/PA Unit representative Fantasia L. Hogan-Bassey-Graham at (571) 776-2210 or via e-mail at Fantasia.L.Hogan-Bassey-Graham@dea.gov, our FOIA Requester Service Center at (571) 776-2300, or e-mail your correspondence to DEA.FOIA@dea.gov. In addition, you may wish to visit our website at www.dea.gov to determine if the information you are requesting is already available to the public.  You may contact our FOIA Public Liaison at (571) 776-2300 for any further assistance and to discuss any aspect of your request.  Additionally, you may contact the Office of Government Information Services (OGIS) at the National Archives and Records Administration to inquire about the FOIA mediation services they offer.  The contact information for OGIS is as follows: Office of Government Information Services, National Archives and Records Administration, Room 2510, 8601 Adelphi Road, College Park, Maryland 20740-6001; e-mail at ogis@nara.gov; telephone at (202) 741-5770; toll free at 1-877-684-6448; or facsimile at (202) 741-5769. Sincerely, 
Fantasia L. Hogan-Bassey-Graham FOIA/PA Specialist Intake Sub-Unit FOIA/PA Unit Drug Enforcement Administration Telephone: (571) 776-2210 E-mail: Fantasia.L.Hogan-Bassey-Graham@dea.gov

communications.subject: DEA FOIA/PA Case Number: 23-00303-F
communications.communication:
Dear William Fernandes:
​
            This e-mail responds to your Freedom of Information Act/Privacy Act (FOIA/PA) request dated April 2, 2022, received by the Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA), FOIA/PA Unit, seeking access to DEA records.  Your request has been opened and assigned the following case number: 23-00303-F.  Please include this case number when communicating with this office.

Your request as written does not meet the requirements of the FOIA, 5 U.S.C. § 552 (a)(3)(A), since they do not reasonably describe records.  The Department of Justice rules, contained at 28 C.F.R. § 16.3, provide that “you must describe the records in enough detail to enable department personnel to locate them with a reasonable amount of effort” and when possible, your request should include specific information about each record sought such as the date, title or name, author and subject matter of the record.  These specifics are important to determine the extent and scope of the search, and to determine the records that are responsive.  DEA can make certain presumptions to overcome some of the deficiencies in your request, but not all of them.

To retrieve the information that you may be seeking requires more specificity.  Under the FOIA, an agency is not required to conduct research.  DEA maintains several types of records and records systems (i.e., regulatory, personnel, investigative, etc.).  For example, in your letter, you are requesting Any and all expense records for travel into the State of Nevada for the period 2020.,” yet you have not specified a particular DEA office that you wish searched; or the type of record that would be responsive to your request.  Be advised that DEA has 239 Domestic Offices in 23 Divisions throughout the United States, and 92 foreign offices in 69 countries, and more than 150 Headquarters Offices.  Since your description did not limit the search to a specific office or area, a vast majority of DEA offices would be tasked to conduct a search of their respective offices for any responsive records pertaining to the subject of your request.  As such, your request is overly broad and burdensome.

Please specify the following:

  1.  Clarify the type of travel (TDY and/or Extended TDY travel)
  2.  Verify the timeframe for “2020” (calendar year Jan-December or fiscal year Oct 2019 – Sept 2020)
  3.  Do you also want the information to include the PCS travel when core employees move?

To this end, no further action will be initiated on this request until we are in receipt of the above documentation.  Upon receipt, we will conduct a query of the Investigative Reporting and Filing System (IRFS).  IRFS is the system of records that contains all administrative, general and investigative files compiled by DEA for law enforcement purposes.  If this office does not receive your response within 30 business days, DEA will assume that you do not wish to pursue this matter and your request will be administratively closed.  Please e-mail your response to fantasia.l.hogan-bassey-graham@dea.gov<mailto:fantasia.l.hogan-bassey-graham@dea.gov>.

If you are not satisfied with DEA’s determination in response to this request, you may administratively appeal by writing to the Director, Office of Information Policy (OIP), United States Department of Justice, 441 G Street, NW, 6th Floor, Washington, D.C. 20530, or you may submit an appeal through OIP's FOIA STAR portal by creating an account following the instructions on OIP’s website:  https://www.justice.gov/oip/submit-and-track-request-or-appeal.  Your appeal must be postmarked or electronically transmitted within 90 days of the date of my response to your request.  If you submit your appeal by mail, both the letter and the envelope should be clearly marked "Freedom of Information Act Appeal."

If you have any questions regarding this email, you may contact our FOIA Requester Service Center at (571) 776-2300.  Thank you for your patience as we work to complete the processing of your request.


Kind regards,

Fantasia Hogan-Bassey-Graham
IBSS Corp. Paralegal II Contractor
DEA Intake Sub-Unit, Freedom of Information and Privacy Act Unit
FOIA and Information Law Section
Drug Enforcement Administration
Attn: FOIA/PA Unit
8701 Morrissette Drive
Springfield, Virginia 22152
P: (571) 776-2210
E: fantasia.l.hogan-bassey-graham@dea.gov<mailto:fantasia.l.hogan-bassey-graham@dea.gov>

title: Florida Book Challenges: Leon County Public Schools

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Florida Book Challenges: Leon County Public Schools
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

1. A copy of any records generated or received pursuant to any policy concerning challenges to curricular, instructional, or library materials. 

2. A copy of any complaints (including informal complaints), and any records generated as a result of the complaints, where the complaint led to a change in status of any book or material in a school library.

3. A copy of any current policy concerning challenges to curricular, instructional, or library materials.

4. A copy of any public records requests received concerning books, library materials, or curricular materials and any records produced in response to the request. 

This request is limited to records generated on or after January 1, 2021.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: Public Records Request
communications.communication:
Good Morning,

We have received your request concerning book challenges.

All challenges are posted on the Leon County Schools Request for Reconsideration webpage https://www.leonschools.net/Page/35368, along with all documentation involved in the process.

Thank you,
Julie

Julie Jernigan
Leon County Schools
Custodian of Records Requests
520 Appleyard Drive
Tallahassee FL 32304
(850) 487-7363

________________________________
*SUNSHINE LAW AND PUBLIC RECORDS CAUTION: Florida has a very broad Public Records Law. Virtually all written communications to or from School Board of Leon County, Florida Personnel are public records available to the public and media upon request. E-mail sent or received on the LCSB system will be considered public and will only be withheld from disclosure if deemed confidential pursuant to State Law. Individual student records are deemed confidential.

communications.subject: Government Records Access and Management Act Request: Records Request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Government Records Access and Management Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am seeking the following information from your  state department of corrections:
List of inmates who identify as transgender or gender diverse (names redacted is fine) and
a. Sex assigned at birth (M/F)
b. Gender identity (M/F)
c. Race
d. Holding Offense information
e. number of transgender male, transgender female, Intersex, gender non-conforming, etc. inmates who have requested placement in institution consistent with their gender identity and status of those requests, and how many inmates currently housed in facility consistent with their gender identity.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Shan Jumper

communications.subject: RE: Government Records Access and Management Act Request: Records Request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

I wanted to follow up on the following Government Records Access and Management Act request, copied below, and originally submitted on Jan. 15, 2024. Please let me know when I can expect to receive a response.

Thanks for your help, and let me know if further clarification is needed.

Hello, 

Thank you for your request. We appreciate your patience. Utah Code 63G-2-201(7) specifies that our agency is not required to create a record or tailor data or information in respond to a records request. However, acknowledging the public interest in the matter of treatment of transgender individuals in the context of the criminal justice/correctional system, we are providing you with some information as a onetime courtesy. 

The Utah Department of Corrections (UDC) Research and Planning team has provided me with the following information to pass on to you: 

-There are 4 female gender assigned at birth offenders and all 4 females identify as male
-There are 30 male gender assigned at birth offenders and all 30 of these males identify as female
-There are only 2 offenders that have requested housing with the gender they identify as. None have been granted as all housing is assigned based on the sex assigned at birth. The Utah State Legislature recently passed a bill addressing the matter of housing assignments for transgender inmates. Please see HB316 (2024). 

Attached to this message is a table showing race and holding offense. For any further questions, we encourage you to reach out to the UDC public information office: https://corrections.utah.gov/media-information/

If you wish to dispute our fulfillment of your records request, you have the right to appeal this decision to the Utah Department of Corrections’ Deputy Director.  To submit a proper appeal, you must file a Notice of Appeal with the Deputy Director within 30 days of the date of this denial.  The Notice of Appeal must contain your name and a copy of, or the original request, which was denied.  It must also include a statement of the relief you seek (explain what you want the Deputy Director to do).  You may also submit a short statement of facts, reasons and legal authority in support of your request for these records.  Please include a mention of the reference number that was assigned to this GRAMA request. 
​
To appeal this request please reply to this message with your appeal. Please also feel free to upload any relevant documents to your appeal to this request. Once we receive your appeal, this request will be reopened while the Deputy Director deliberates.  You may also send your appeal through postal mail to: 
​
Jared Garcia
Deputy Director
Utah Department of Corrections
14717 South Minuteman Drive
Draper, UT  84020

In addition, please be aware that records requests can also be made on the UDC website at: https://corrections.utah.gov/records-requests/

Please reach out if you have any questions or concerns. 

Best,
Tavin Forsythe-Barker
GRAMA Records Officer
Utah Department of Corrections

communications.communication:

Pursuant to the Colorado Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

A CSV export of your agency's Shared Mailboxes (see https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/admin/email/about-shared-mailboxes?view=o365-worldwide for more info ) including the following parameters for every shared mailbox:

- Primary SMTP Address
- Date Created

A simple way to retrieve this is by having a member of IT (such as a System Administrator) run the following command in Exchange Online PowerShell (if email is hosted in a Microsoft Exchange environment):

Get-Mailbox -ResultSize Unlimited -RecipientTypeDetails SharedMailbox | Select Name,PrimarySmtpAddress,WhenCreated | Export-CSV -Path .\SharedMailboxes_$((Get-Date).ToString('MM-dd-yyyy_hh-mm-ss')).csv

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

J Ader

communications.subject: RE: Nevada Public Records Act Request: Lyon County Sheriff - Drone Program
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

I wanted to follow up on the following Nevada Public Records Act request, copied below, and originally submitted on Feb. 26, 2024. Please let me know when I can expect to receive a response.

Thanks for your help, and let me know if further clarification is needed.

Mr. Capuano, 

The Lyon County Sheriff’s Office is in receipt of your public records request to obtain information about the Unmanned Aerial System.

I have reviewed the request and determined that some of the information you requested is available now, and attached to this email, however there are other parts that will take time to research and get transferred to the proper medium for release. The Lyon County Sheriff’s Office cannot fulfill this request within five (5) business days by March 12, 2024.  This is notice serves that the Sheriff’s Office is unable to make the public record available by that date and the earliest date and time the Lyon County Sheriff’s Office  reasonably  believes the public records will  be  available  for  you to  inspect  or  copy  or  after  which  a copy of the public book or record will be available to the ACLU of Nevada is April 5, 2024.   

The Sheriff’s Office desires to make a reasonable effort to assist you to focus the request  in  such  a  manner  as  to  maximize  the  likelihood  you  will  be  able  to  inspect,  copy  or  receive  a  copy  of  the public records requested as expeditiously as possible.  If you have specific dates or names or other information, that will allow us to expedite the search on our end, or if you can narrow the search to include specific types of information.  This notice and request is made pursuant to NRS 239.0107.

Thank you for your continued cooperation in this matter. 

Attached to this correspondence:
-All Part 107 certifications for agency UAS operators.
-All FAA and Nevada Department of Public Safety UAS registrations (See attached document)


There is no written request for UAS operation that I am aware of, the requests are made as needed and contact is made by our dispatch center via phone or radio. I have requested the the flight logs for our UAS program for 2023, once I have those I will upload them to you. 

Sincerely,

Commander Ryan Powell
Lyon County Sheriff’s Office

communications.subject: Massachusetts Public Records Law Request: Public Records Request for Data on School Policing (Bellingham Police Department)
communications.communication:
To whoever it may concern: 

This letter constitutes a request pursuant to the Public Records Act, G.L. c.66, §10, for public records in the custody of your school district. Under the Criminal Justice Reform Act,  school districts and law enforcement agencies must “specify the manner and division of responsibility for collecting and reporting the school-based arrests, citations and court referrals of students to the Department of Elementary and Secondary Education” (DESE).   DESE began collecting data on school-related arrests in the 2018-19 school year. In the 2019-20 school year, DESE has expanded that collection to include data on all referrals to law enforcement.  DESE has defined these terms as follows, borrowing the same definitions used by the U.S. Department of Education since its 2009 Civil Rights Data Collection.  

A school-related arrest “[r]efers to an arrest of a student for any activity conducted on school grounds, during off campus school activities (including while taking school transportation), or due to a referral by any school official. All school-related arrests are considered referrals to law enforcement.”  

A referral to law enforcement “[i]s an action by which a student is reported to any law enforcement agency or official, including a school police unit, for an incident that occurs on school grounds, during school-related events, or while taking school transportation, regardless of whether official action is taken. Citations, tickets, court referrals, and school-related arrests are considered referrals to law enforcement.”   


I request the following public records, as defined in G. L. c. 4, § 7 (twenty-sixth): 

1.	An extract of your records management system or database that includes each school-related arrest and each referral to law enforcement conducted during the 2018-2019, 2019-2020, 2020-2021, and 2021-2022 school year (up until the day the records are produced). Specifically, we request an extract of the database to include the following columns:
a.	Date of arrest or referral to law enforcement
b.	Time of arrest or referral to law enforcement
c.	Charge (or charges)
d.	Whether the individual(s) was arrested or referred to law enforcement
e.	Sex of individual(s) arrested or referred to law enforcement
f.	Age of individual(s) arrested or referred to law enforcement
g.	Race of individual(s) arrested or referred to law enforcement
h.	Ethnicity of individual(s) arrested or referred to law enforcement
i.	Disability status of the individual(s) arrested or referred to law enforcement
j.	Whether the individual arrested or referred to law enforcement is a student at the school.
k.	Name of arresting officer, if applicable, and 
l.	Badge number of the arresting officer or the officer that referred the youth to law enforcement, as applicable.

2.	If such an extract of the database in question 1 is not possible, please provide school incident reports on each school-related arrest and referral to law enforcement conducted during the 2018-2019, 2019-2020, 2020-2021, and 2021-2022 school year (up until the day the records are produced). 

3.	A copy of any active standard operating procedures developed with the police department and/or other law enforcement agencies regarding police placement or activity in your corresponding school;  and,

4.	Any records instructing or informing police personnel of, or otherwise describing data reporting requirements and procedures for complying with G.L. c. 71 § 37P(b).

5.	The cost to the school district of assigning a school resource officer to each school; and, 

6.	The total number of school resource officers and total number of guidance counselors for each school in your district for school years 2018-2019, 2019-2020, 2020-2021, and,

7.	The total number and a brief description of 911 calls from schools in your district to local police departments conducted during the 2018-2019, 2019-2020, 2020-2021, and 2021-2022, and, 

8.	A description of the proposed budget for mental, social, or emotional health support personnel for the school district.

As this request involves a matter of public interest and will not be used for any commercial purpose, we ask that all fees associated with this request be waived pursuant to 950 C.M.R. 32.07(2)(k). The purpose of this request is to determine whether your school district and police department are complying with their reporting obligations under the Criminal Justice Reform Act.  “The public has an interest in knowing whether public servants are carrying out their duties in an efficient and law-abiding manner.”    

It would be ill-advised to impose a fee for data that your school district may have failed to report in violation of statutory and regulatory duty.  Moreover, as you know, municipalities with a population of over 20,000 may not assess a fee for the first 2 hours of time spent searching for, compiling, segregating, redacting and reproducing a requested record. Finally, pursuant to 950 C.M.R. 32.07(2)(i), a records access officer shall assess no fee greater than the lowest hourly rate of a person capable of compiling, segregating, redacting and reproducing a requested record. In the event that a charge is incurred for this request which you will not waive, please so indicate and include an itemization of estimated good faith costs.
 
Please provide public records to a requestor in an electronic format unless the record is not available in an electronic format. G.L.c. 66, § 6A(d). 

The Public Records Act requires that you comply with this request within ten (10) business days following receipt. If you believe that documents or data responsive to any request herein is not public record and thus not subject to disclosure, please set forth in writing the specific reasons for such assertion, including the specific exemption or exemptions that you believe apply.  To the extent that you determine that records need to be redacted in order to be produced under any law protecting the privacy of named individuals, please do so rather than withholding them in their entirety.

If you have any questions about this request, or need additional time to respond, please contact me by phone at (617)-373-5862 or by email at k.stathulis@northeastern.edu. Thank you in advance for your prompt response to this request.
	
Sincerely, 


Katherine Stathulis, Esq.
Center for Public Interest, Advocacy, and Collaboration
Northeastern University School of Law

RE: County Manager's Office of March 25, 2024, Reference # M000213-032524 Dear Requestor, The Volusia County Florida received a public records request from you on March 25, 2024. Your request mentioned: To Whom It May Concern: 
Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following public records: 
Please provide me with a list, preferably in Excel format, of the Volusia County government employee names, job titles and description, and their monthly salaries from January 1st, 2022 to the present date, for the following departments and divisions including but not limited to: 
1) Volusia County Council 
2) Volusia County Growth and Resource Management 
3) Volusia County Building and Code Administration 
4) Volusia County Contractor Licensing and Construction Appeals Board 
5) Volusia County Code Compliance 
6) Volusia County Building and Permit Center 
7) Volusia County Contractor Licensing 
If possible, I would respectfully ask that any fees be waived as this information is of interest to the general public. The requested information will be made available to the general public, as well as to news and media outlets, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 
In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. 
Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 21 days or sooner. 
Sincerely, 
Lourdes Gonzalez The Volusia County Florida has reviewed its files and has located responsive records to your request. communications.subject: Volusia County Growth and Resource Management :: G000265-040124
communications.communication:
--- Please respond above this line --- 
RE: Growth and Resource Management of April 01, 2024, Reference # G000265-040124 Dear Lourdes Gonzalez, The Volusia County Florida received a public records request from you on April 01, 2024. Your request mentioned: Please provide the following information as it pertains to Volusia County Building & Code Administration's requests for disconnecting existing electrical utility service, source of energy, fuel or power, to customers of Duke Energy Corporation, Volusia County: 
1) Written guidelines, including the relevant sections of Florida Building Code(s) and Volusia County Municipal Code of Ordinance, authorizing a utility disconnection by Code Enforcement officials. 
2) Standard operation procedures followed when requesting the disconnection of utility service, energy, fuel or power to customers of Duke Energy Corporation, Volusia County. 
3) The basis for establishing a reasonable cause of action or determination for disconnecting utility service, energy, fuel or power by Code Enforcement officials to customers of Duke Energy Corporation, Volusia County. 
4) The number of disconnect requests that have been made to Duke Energy Corporation by Volusia County Building & Code Administration for the period January 1, 2022 through present. 
5) The property addresses where disconnect requests have been made by Volusia County Building & Code Administration to Duke Energy Corporation, Volusia County, and the ticket numbers. 
6) The number of Notices of Violation, Notice of Hearings, and Stop Work Orders that have been issued in relation to Code Enforcement requests for utility service power disconnects, for the period January 1, 2022 through present, and the corresponding case numbers. 
7) The name of the Code Enforcement building official(s) who have signed off on the disconnect requests to Duke Energy Corporation, Volusia County. 
I also request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge, processed by a representative of the news media/press, and is not for commercial usage. 
In the event that fees cannot be waived, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. 
I would prefer the request be filed electronically, by e-mail attachment if available. 
Should my request be refused, kindly provide the specific legislative citation for the rejection, as required by Section 119.07(1)(d) of the Florida Statutes. 
Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within a reasonable time frame, according to Section 119.07(1)(a),(c) of the Florida Statutes. 
Good afternoon Ms. Gonzalez, 
Your requests have been idle for over 2 weeks due to non-payment. We have received no response, nor any attempts at payment. We will be closing this request now due to this and if you would like to still have these records you will need to request the records again, and we will go through the process again. This will start the process all the way over and you will be at the back of the line due to this. 
Should you have any questions please reach out to the Growth and Resource Management Department. 
Sincerely, 
Growth and Resource Management For questions or additional information, please reply to this email. Sincerely, Growth and Resource Management 
To monitor the progress or update this request please log into the Volusia County Public Records Center (https://u8387778.ct.sendgrid.net/ls/click?upn=u001.VEsWrlMiJDg0mXafq1mEXWDKepqlOChcQFHy-2FUPvjaMy8mSuzZEEjDxFEvl4lgXSFBjje9RqQzr7q4slu0tc4zXV5dKxVoSVPluavFuW7DY-3DBinf_4tSNN5NEkJmfbwYNFjfHV62QVFM56YKfJZK7ZvmZCB-2BEEY1yBcpkjVfYkfCludiiTG8sJQfuqOO6RWRsG8BoTaeS1xSrRxx4qMnXU40D7J-2Ft0NCECIK4GSXGFztaqwRzYsjtdy-2BAy8ZHCudt2Gmkn9XD25nC-2BJFRaPNheOxlm4IfcyDydzkwtDDF5QBdihr9X-2BnRPvaO7rTZAxJyiH9qoNyLB6cbr0G8XdRNUwjmVHDyVclegJzJupuugN-2Bk7r7UcK0-2FeqU2H-2Fj-2FIx-2BYxBCvOrK2P95w-2BCZaqOLcW2RsTSn9mYqFWdcE8VFLQGb8tViA3ODciCZl7VCRAoChuHw44jzYRDflzm02a-2BK5fLEmk2E0D55t8m8zTSzwFxmOfp1N)
